<P>Anno Regni GEORGII II. REGIS</P>
<P><HI>Magnae Britanniae, Franciae, &amp; Hiberniae,</HI> DECIMO TERTIO.</P>
<P>At the Parliament begun and holden at <HI>Westminster, Anno Dom.</HI> 1740. In the Thirteenth Year of the Reign of Our Sovereign Lord <HI>GEORGE</HI> the Second, by the Grace of God, of <HI>Great Britain, France,</HI>and <HI>Ireland,</HI> King, Defender of the Faith, <HI>&amp;c.</HI></P>
<P><FIGURE>
</FIGURE></P>
<P><HI>LONDON,</HI> Printed by <HI>John <GAP DESC="illegible" REASON="indecipherable" EXTENT="1 word">,</HI> Printer to the King's most Excellent Majesty, 1740.</P>
<P><HI>NEW-LONDON,</HI> Re-printed by <HI>Timothy <GAP DESC="illegible" REASON="indecipherable" EXTENT="1 word">,</HI> Printer to the Governour and Company of His Majesty's <HI>English</HI> Colony of <HI>Connecticut</HI> in <HI>New-England,</HI> 1751.</P>
